Please join us for the Charleston High School Homecoming Parade Friday, October 5th starting at 4pm! Along with our CHS Mighty Tigers Football Players, Cheerleaders, Student Organizations, CHS Alumni and members of the community, you can see our BEAUTIFUL 2018 Homecoming Court.

Homecoming festivities at the school will begin promptly at 6:00 p.m. on the football field with the presentation of the Homecoming Court and the Crowning of the 2018 CHS Homecoming Queen, followed by an exciting football game as the Charleston Tigers take on the JZ George Jaguars.

post_text:
We are pleased to announce that Parents and Guardians can now create an ActiveParent account ONLINE!

Just go to our District WebSite at http://www.etsd.k12.ms.us/ and click on the link to ActiveParent on the left side of the page. On the ActiveParent Login page, click on "Create an ActiveParent Account". There will be step-by-step instructions for creating your account and then adding your students.

We encourage every parent to create an account and have instant access to your student's grades, attendance, and other information. Thank You for your interest in your child's education!!!

ALL TEACHERS and ETSD EMPLOYEES PLEASE REPORT TO THE MORGAN FREEMAN AUDITORIUM AT CHARLESTON HIGH SCHOOL on FRIDAY AUGUST 3rd AT 9:30 AM FOR THE BACK TO SCHOOL CONVOCATION.
ATTENDANCE BY ALL EMPLOYEES IS MANDATORY.

Due to District Calendar modifications, ETSD Teachers' first full day of school will be Friday, August 3rd. Teachers will report back for additional professional development Monday August 6th and Tuesday August 7th. All teachers check with your school administrators for "school" reporting time.

Students' first day of school will be Wednesday August 8th. This will be a FULL DAY.
